===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
{{Han compound|人|又|ls=ic|t1=person|t2=hand}} – a hand grabbing a person.

===Etymology 1===
Possibly connected to {{cog|my|ကပ်||to arrive at}} or {{cog|kac|khap||to carry, to reach}} ({{zh-ref|Starostin and Peiros, 1996}}) or less likely to {{cog|bo|འགྲུབ་པ}} ~ {{m|bo|འགྲུབ||to make ready}}, {{m|bo|སྒྲུབ་པ}} ~ {{m|bo|བསྒྲུབ||to complete, achieve}}, {{m|bo|གྲུབ་པ||complete}} ({{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2007}}).

Possibly departing tone derivations are {{zh-l|暨|to attain, to reach}}, {{zh-l|迄|to reach to}}, and {{zh-l|既|already}} ({{zh-ref|Yu, 1948}}, {{zh-ref|Baxter, 1992}}). However, see those entries for more.

